#### **Step 3: Upload to GitHub**

Now you can safely upload your code.

1.  **Initialize Git:** Open your command prompt in your project folder and run:
    ```bash
    git init
    ```
2.  **Add and Commit:**
    ```bash
    git add .
    git commit -m "Initial commit of Document QnA RAG system"
    ```
3.  **Create and Link a GitHub Repository:**
    * Go to [GitHub](https://github.com/) and create a new, empty repository.
    * Copy the commands they provide under "...or push an existing repository..." and run them in your command prompt. They will look like this:
        ```bash
        git remote add origin https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
        git branch -M main
        git push -u origin main
        ```

Your code is now safely on GitHub without any of your secrets!

